<h1>Dashboard</h1>

<h2>Welcome <%= @user.name %></h2>

<section class="image-search">
  <p>
    <%= form_tag "/search", method: :get do %>
    <%= label_tag :search %>
    <%= text_field_tag :search, nil, placeholder: 'Keyword'%>

    <%= submit_tag "Search" %>
    <% end %>
  </p>
</section>

<div class="card text-white bg-info mb-3" style="max-width: 30rem;">
  <div class="card-header">Don't know what to do?</div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Instructions:</h5>
    <p class="card-text">
    1. Enter a keyword into the search bar above and hit search.<br><br>
    2. GlitchCraft will render two images for your choosing:<br></p>
    <p style="margin-left: 40px">a. The Corrupt AI Image is an AI generated image from scratch based off it's perception of your keyword.<br>
    b. The Pixel Panic Image is a human tagged image relating to your keyword.<br></p>
    3. Select your image and cause a glitch!<br>
    <br>
    NOTE: If you do not like your image selections, simply hit the back button on your browser and create a new search!
  </div>
</div>
